# Markdown to PDF — use internal scripts only

> **Source of truth:** [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) §3. Keep this file in sync when editing.

When a study markdown file under `Studies/<Slug>/` needs a PDF, **always** use the
repository pipeline. Do not substitute pandoc, `markdown-pdf`, VS Code export,
hand-written Puppeteer scripts, or other one-off converters.

## One-time setup

```powershell
pip install -r requirements.txt
cd Scripts
npm install
cd ..
```

Required for all PDFs (Puppeteer). **Mermaid diagrams** additionally need the `mermaid`
npm package installed in `Scripts/`.

## Regenerate one study (preferred)

```powershell
python Scripts/_regenerate_pdf.py <Slug>
```

Reads **Status:** from the markdown, applies the Draft watermark when appropriate,
and runs verification after PDF export.

## Internal pipeline

`_regenerate_pdf.py` calls:

1. **`Scripts/_convert_to_pdf.py`** — markdown → styled HTML; ` ```mermaid ` → `<div class="mermaid">`; fenced code uses `pre-wrap`.
2. **`Scripts/_html_to_pdf.js`** — render Mermaid to SVG, then HTML → PDF via Puppeteer.
3. **`Scripts/_verify_pdf_diagrams.py`** — fail if raw Mermaid syntax (e.g. `flowchart TD`) appears in the PDF.
4. **`Scripts/_verify_pdf_fenced_code.py`** — fail if fenced code/spec lines are clipped (e.g. `[compound]` → `[c`).

Manual single-study steps (only if needed):

```powershell
python Scripts/_convert_to_pdf.py Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.md
node Scripts/_html_to_pdf.js Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.html Draft
python Scripts/_verify_pdf_diagrams.py Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.md Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.pdf
python Scripts/_verify_pdf_fenced_code.py Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.md Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.pdf
Remove-Item Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.html
```

- **`Draft`** watermark argument — required for **Draft** studies. Omit for **Released**.
- **Delete the intermediate `.html`** after PDF generation.

## What the scripts provide (do not reimplement)

- Study typography, tables, blockquotes, and print CSS — `_convert_to_pdf.py`
- **Fully justified body paragraphs** — `_convert_to_pdf.py`
- **Embedded raster figures** — PNG images in the study directory — `_convert_to_pdf.py`
- **Mermaid diagrams** — fenced ` ```mermaid ` blocks rendered as SVG — `_convert_to_pdf.py` + `_html_to_pdf.js`
- **Fenced code/spec blocks** — `white-space: pre-wrap` on `<pre>` so long lines wrap; verified by `_verify_pdf_fenced_code.py`. Prefer **tables** for wide multi-column specs.
- **`**Status:**` omitted from PDF body** — watermark shows Draft/Released
- Footer: `AnalyticMadhyasthDarshan.org` and page numbers — `_html_to_pdf.js`

## Regenerate all studies

```powershell
$studies = Get-ChildItem Studies -Directory
foreach ($s in $studies) {
  python Scripts/_regenerate_pdf.py $s.Name
}
```

## After conversion

- Confirm `Studies/<Slug>/<Slug>.pdf` exists.
- If the study uses Mermaid, confirm diagrams rendered (verify runs automatically).
- If the study uses long ` ```text ` blocks, confirm lines are not clipped (verify runs automatically).
- Refresh `**Edited on:**` and catalogs per [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) §1–§2 when content changed.

## Do not

- Edit PDFs directly or commit hand-built HTML as source of truth.
- Add Mermaid without ensuring `Scripts/npm install` has been run.
- Put wide formal specs in ` ```text ` when a table would fit — monospace lines clip without `pre-wrap`.
- Change conversion behavior inline in chat without updating these scripts when the change should apply to all future PDFs.
